Sprint 7 Phase 3 baseline screenshot directory.

Baseline PNGs are generated by `npm run test:e2e:update-snapshots`
when the harness is run against the Vite dev server with a working
Playwright chromium browser. Phase 3 QA could not generate the PNGs
in the dispatched environment (Playwright execution was blocked by
the agent's bash sandbox); the directory is committed as the
allow-list anchor so future runs can drop screenshots here.

To populate baselines locally:
  1. npm install (Playwright chromium installs automatically per
     playwright.config.ts webServer.command).
  2. npx playwright install chromium  (if browser not yet cached)
  3. npm run dev  (background — Vite dev server on :5173)
  4. Remove the `test.skip` markers in tests/e2e/sprint7-faz-smoke.spec.ts
     OR change `test.skip(` to `test(` once renderer-window.api mock
     can be verified to drive the destruction-director through all
     Faz cycles end-to-end.
  5. npm run test:e2e:update-snapshots

The 14 (T01..T14 + T15 reduced-motion) expected files:
  T01-lobby.png
  T02-bang-fired.png
  T03-faz0-bang.png
  T04-faz1-critical-dialog.png
  T05-faz2-takeover.png
  T06-faz3-terminal.png
  T07-faz4-file-wipe.png
  T08-faz5-disk-format.png
  T09-faz6-bsod.png
  T10-faz8-reveal-mid.png
  T11-faz8-son-ekran.png
  T12-tekrar-cycle.png
  T13-pre-cik-click.png
  (T14 + T15 are spy/computed-style assertions; no screenshot)

See ../../../.claude/cache/handoffs/sprint7/phase3-qa.md for the
full Phase 3 QA verdict + the KNOWN-LIMITED notes.
